To find the value of $b$, we can use the fact that $-4$ is a solution to the equation $x^2 + bx - 36 = 0$. This means that when $x = -4$, the equation evaluates to $0$. We can substitute $x = -4$ into the equation to find the value of $b$. 
\begin{align*}
(-4)^2 + (-4)b - 36 &= 0 \\
16 - 4b - 36 &= 0 \\
-4b &= 20 \\
b &= \boxed{-5}
\end{align*}
